Tori Spelling was a trouper at Benihana's Japanese Restaurant in Encino, California when she tripped and fell onto a hot grill used to prepare food in front of customers .
She shouted out in pain from a large burn on her right arm .
Spelling was taken to the Grossman Burn Center at the West Hills Hospital for treatment .
It was determined that she had a severe burn and suggested they remove the damaged skin and graft skin from another area of the body .